text: Bjørnar Moxnes (born 19 December 1981) is a Norwegian politician and activist. He is a critic of the European Union. In 2012, he became Leader of the Red Party. In 2017, he was elected to the Storting.Dagsavisen: Den røde og ranke ==References== Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Oslo
